<section xml:id="S_proportions">
  <title>Proportional Reasoning Every Day</title>

  <subsection>
  <title>Overview</title>
  
  
    <p>
      We have seen that algebra arises in making introductions, the 100s chart, number and magic number puzzles, children's literature, and Aesop's fable. Now we examine contexts that arise in our daily experiences.
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <worksheet top="1in" right="1.2in" left="1.2in" bottom="1in" xml:id="act-recipes">
    <title>Recipes and Proportional Reasoning</title>
    
    <introduction>
      <p>
        A proportional relationship that frequently arises in daily life is scaling recipes. As you work on <xref text="title" ref="act-recipes"/>, think about these questions: What does slope mean in this context? How can we find the slope in each representation, context, table, graph, and equation? How are the slopes for each of the ingredients in the guacamole recipe related?
      </p>
    </introduction>

